							<body  ><div class="section"><p class="VoteReason">A party vote was called for on the question,<em> That the </em><em>Social Security (Stopping Benefit Payments for Offenders who Repeatedly Fail to Comply with Community Sentences) Amendment Bill be now read a first time</em><em>.</em></p><p class="VoteCount"><strong>Ayes 61</strong></p><p class="VoteText">New Zealand National 59; ACT New Zealand 1; United Future 1.</p><p class="VoteCount"><strong>Noes 60</strong></p><p class="VoteText">New Zealand Labour 32; Green Party 14; New Zealand First 12; Māori Party 2.</p><p class="VoteResult">Bill read a first time. </p><p class="IndentMarginalone">Bill referred to the Social Services Committee.</p></div></body>
